SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT
THIS AMENDED AND RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this ???Agreement???), is entered into as of December 28, 2021 (the ???Execution Date???), by and between Jicarilla Solar 1 LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (???Jicarilla Solar 1???), Jicarilla Solar 2 LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (???Jicarilla Solar 2???) and Jicarilla Storage 1 LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (???Jicarilla Storage 1???, and together with Jicarilla Solar 1 and Jicarilla Solar 2, the ???Parties??? and each a ???Party???).
RECITALS
A. Jicarilla Solar 1 is developing and will own and operate a solar generation facility (the ???Jicarilla Solar 1 Project???) with a nameplate capacity of approximately 50 MW (the ???Jicarilla Solar 1 Permitted Capacity???);
B. Jicarilla Solar 2 is developing and will own and operate a solar generation facility (the ???Jicarilla Solar 2 Project???) with a nameplate capacity of approximately 50 MW (the ???Jicarilla Solar 2 Permitted Capacity???);
C. Jicarilla Storage 1 is developing and will own and operate a battery energy storage facility (the ???Jicarilla Storage 1 Project??? ) with a nameplate capacity of approximately 20 MW (the ???Jicarilla Storage 1 Permitted Capacity???);
D. Each Party has entered or will enter into a Transmission Construction and Interconnection Agreement (the ???TCIA???) with the Jicarilla Apache Nation (the ???Nation???). Nation owns and operates an electric utility operated by the Jicarilla Apache Nation Power Authority (the ???JANPA) which provides for the interconnection of each Party???s respective Project to the electric transmission system of JANPA (the ???JANPA Transmission System???);
E. The Jicarilla Solar 1 Project, the Jicarilla Solar 2 Project and the Jicarilla Storage 1 Project (collectively the ???Projects??? and each a ???Project???) will each interconnect to the JANPA Transmission System through the same Point of Interconnection as defined in their respective TCIAs;
F. It is anticipated that one or more Subsequent Projects (as defined below) will also interconnect to the JANPA Transmission System through such Point of Interconnection;
G. Jicarilla Solar 2 will own and operate certain personal property, fixtures, equipment and/or facilities (including the Interconnection Customer???s Interconnection Facilities, as identified in Appendix A to the Jicarilla Solar 2 TCIA) described in Exhibit A attached hereto (the ???Shared Facilities???) that are necessary to interconnect each of the Projects and each Subsequent Project, if any, to the JANPA Transmission System and to deliver electric energy to the JANPA Transmission System; and
1
H. The Parties are entered into the Shared Facilities Agreement dated August 3, 2021 (???Initial SFA???) to allow each of Jicarilla Solar 1 and Jicarilla Storage 1, and each Subsequent Project Owner (as defined below), if any, to use the Shared Facilities as necessary for it to be able to operate its Project or Projects and deliver energy to and withdraw energy from the JANPA Transmission System.
I. The Parties wish to amend and restate the Initial SFA via this Agreement to clarify certain provisions.
NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows:
1. Definitions and Rules of Interpretation
1.1 Defined Terms. As used in this Agreement, the following defined terms have the meanings indicated below:
???Access Notice??? has the meaning set forth in Section 3.3(i).
???Affected Party??? has the meaning set forth in Section 5.3(i).
???Affiliate??? means as to any Person, any other Person which directly or indirectly controls, or is under common control with, or is controlled by, such Person. As used in this definition, ???control??? (including its correlative meanings, ???controlled by??? and ???under common control with???) with respect to any Person means the possession, directly or indirectly, of the power to direct or cause the direction of the management and policies of such Person, whether through the ownership of voting securities or member or partnership interests, by contract or otherwise.
???Agreement??? has the meaning set forth in the Preamble.
???Applicable Laws and Regulations??? means all duly promulgated applicable federal, state, local, and Tribal laws, regulations, rules, ordinances, codes, decrees, judgments, directives, or judicial or administrative orders, permits and other duly authorized actions of any Governmental Authority.
???Applicable Reliability Standards??? means the requirements and guidelines of North American Electric Reliability Corporation or its successor organization and the reliability council applicable to the Transmission System to which the Projects are directly interconnected.
???Breach??? means the failure of a Party to perform or observe any material term or condition of this Agreement
???Breaching Party??? has the meaning set forth in Section 8.1.
2
???Connect???, ???Connecting???, ???Connected???, or ???Connection??? means, with respect to a Project, the connection of such Project to the Shared Facilities in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement.
???Connected Party??? has the meaning set forth in Section 5.3(i).
???Connecting Party??? has the meaning set forth in Section 3.3(i).
???Costs??? has the meaning set forth in Section 5.2(i).
???Disclosing Party??? has the meaning set forth in Section 12.17.
???Effective Date??? has the meaning set forth in Section 2.1.
???Execution Date??? has the meaning set forth in the Preamble.
???FERC??? means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission or any successor agency.
???FPA??? means the Federal Power Act, as amended
???Force Majeure Event??? has the meaning set forth in Section 10.1.
???Good Utility Practice??? means any of the practices, methods and acts engaged in or approved by a significant portion of the electric industry during the relevant time period, or any of the practices, methods and acts which, in the exercise of reasonable judgment in light of the facts known at the time the decision was made, could have been expected to accomplish the desired result at a reasonable cost consistent with good business practices, reliability, safety and expedition. Good Utility Practice is not intended to be limited to the optimum practice, method, or act to the exclusion of all others, but rather to be acceptable practices, methods, or acts generally accepted in the region.
???Governmental Authority??? means shall mean any federal, state, local, or other governmental regulatory or administrative agency, court, commission, department, board, or other governmental subdivision, legislature, rulemaking board, tribunal, or other governmental authority having jurisdiction over the Parties, their respective facilities, or the respective services they provide, and exercising or entitled to exercise any administrative, executive, police, or taxing authority or power.
???Information??? has the meaning set forth in Section 12.17.
???Interruption??? has the meaning set forth in Section 5.3(i).
???JANPA??? has the meaning set forth in Recital D.
???JANPA Transmission System??? has the meaning set forth in Recital D.
???Jicarilla Solar 1??? has the meaning set forth in the Preamble. 3
???Jicarilla Solar 1 Permitted Capacity??? has the meaning set forth in Recital A.
???Jicarilla Solar 1 Project??? has the meaning set forth in Recital A.
???Jicarilla Solar 2??? has the meaning set forth in the Preamble.
???Jicarilla Solar 2 Permitted Capacity??? has the meaning set forth in Recital B.
???Jicarilla Solar 2 Project??? has the meaning set forth in Recital B.
???Jicarilla Storage 1??? has the meaning set forth in the Preamble.
???Jicarilla Storage 1 Permitted Capacity??? has the meaning set forth in Recital C.
???Jicarilla Storage 1 Project??? has the meaning set forth in Recital C.
???MW??? means megawatts expressed in AC, unless otherwise defined.
???Net Revenue Losses??? has the meaning set forth in Section 5.3(ii).
???Non-Breaching Party??? has the meaning set forth in Section 8.1.
???Operating Project??? or ???Operating Projects??? mean, individually or collectively, as appropriate the Project or Subsequent Project of: (i) Jicarilla Solar 2 or (ii) any Sharing Party as of the Use Right Date set forth in such Sharing Party???s Use Exercise Notice.
???Party??? and ???Parties??? have the meanings set forth in the Preamble, and includes any other Sharing Party that executes a Joinder pursuant to the terms of this Agreement.
???Permitted Capacity???, means, individually or collectively, the Jicarilla Solar 1 Permitted Capacity, the Jicarilla Solar 2 Permitted Capacity, the Jicarilla Storage 1 Permitted Capacity and any Subsequent Project Permitted Capacity.
???Person??? means any individual, partnership, joint stock company, corporation, limited liability company, trust, unincorporated association or joint venture, any Governmental Authority, or any other entity.
???Project??? and ???Projects??? have the meanings set forth in Recital E.
???Pro Rata Share??? has the meaning set forth in Section 5.2(i).
???Rate Schedule Filing??? has the meaning set forth in Section 7.2.
???Shared Facilities??? has the meaning set forth in Recital G.
4
???Sharing Party??? means each of Jicarilla Solar 1, Jicarilla Storage 1 and, upon execution and delivery of a Joinder in accordance with Section 2.2, each Subsequent Project Owner, if any.
???Subsequent Project??? means any renewable energy generation or energy storage project that (i) requires the use of the Shared Facilities in order to be connected to the JANPA Transmission System (ii) is to be located on land leased from the Jicarilla Apache Nation in accordance with a lease agreement that has been executed and delivered by the Subsequent Project Owner and the Jicarilla Apache Nation, which lease agreement has been approved by the Bureau of Indian Affairs and (iii) has a Permitted Capacity which, when added to the Permitted Capacities of all other Subsequent Projects in respect of which Joinders have been executed, does not exceed 70 MW.
???Subsequent Project Owner??? means a Person who owns a Subsequent Project.
???Subsequent Project Permitted Capacity??? means the nameplate capacity of a Subsequent Project as set forth in the Joinder executed in respect of such Subsequent Project.
???TCIA??? has the meaning set forth in Recital D.
???Total Permitted Capacity??? means the sum of the Jicarilla Solar 1 Permitted Capacity, the Jicarilla Solar 2 Permitted Capacity, the Jicarilla Storage 1 Permitted Capacity, and each Subsequent Project Permitted Capacity
???Use Exercise Notice??? has the meaning set forth in Section 3.2.
???Use Right Date??? has the meaning set forth in Section 3.2.
1.2 Rules of Interpretation.
(a) All article, section, schedule, and exhibit references used in this Agreement are to articles, sections, schedules and exhibits of or to this Agreement unless otherwise specified. The schedules and exhibits attached to this Agreement constitute a part of this Agreement and are incorporated herein for all purposes.
(b) If a term is defined as one part of speech (such as a noun), it shall have a corresponding meaning when used as another part of speech (such as a verb). Terms defined in the singular have the corresponding meanings in the plural, and vice versa. Unless the context of this Agreement clearly requires otherwise, words importing the masculine gender shall include the feminine and neutral genders and vice versa. The term ???includes??? or ???including??? shall mean ???including without limitation.??? The words ???hereof,??? ???hereto,??? ???hereby,??? ???herein,??? ???hereunder??? and words of similar import, when used in this Agreement, shall refer to this Agreement as a whole and not to any particular section or article in which such words appear. The word ???or??? shall not be exclusive.
5
(c) This Agreement shall be construed without regard to any presumption or rule requiring construction or interpretation against the drafting Party or the Party causing any instrument to be drafted.
(d) The captions and headings in this Agreement are for convenience only and shall not be considered a part of or affect the construction or interpretation of any provision of this Agreement.
2. EFFECTIVE DATE; TERM; EARLY TERMINATION
2.1 Effective Date. This Agreement shall become effective upon execution by each of the Parties (the ???Effective Date???); provided, however, that if any portion of this Agreement requires acceptance by FERC under Applicable Laws and Regulations in order to become effective, such portion shall be subject to such acceptance. Once effective, this Agreement shall supersede the Initial SFA in all respects.
2.2 Joinder of Subsequent Project Owners. A Person that is a proposed Subsequent Project Owner may become a party to this Agreement and a Sharing Party by executing a Joinder substantially in the form of Exhibit B, accompanied by evidence reasonably satisfactory to Jicarilla Solar 2, that the project to be owned by the proposed Subsequent Project Owner and Connected to the Shared Facilities meets the criteria of a Subsequent Project set forth in the definition thereof and such Connection will not have an adverse impact on any other Operating Project.
2.3 Term. The term of this Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall continue in effect until terminated (a) by mutual agreement of the Parties, or (b) pursuant to Section 2.4 of this Agreement.
2.4 Early Termination. This Agreement shall automatically terminate, without further action by any Party and without further liability of any Party to any other Party (except for obligations accruing prior to the termination), upon the date that all Sharing Parties shall have permanently ceased operation of their respective Operating Projects.
3. GRANT OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS
3.1 Grant. Jicarilla Solar 2 hereby grants to each Sharing Party, during the term of this Agreement, and on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the non-exclusive right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities as may be reasonably necessary for such Sharing Party???s ownership, operation and maintenance of its respective Operating Project, including in connection with the delivery of energy to and the receipt of energy from the JANPA Transmission System up to each Operating Project???s Permitted Capacity.
3.2 Operating Projects No Sharing Party shall have any right to use the Shared Facilities, nor any responsibility or obligation for any Costs with respect thereto, until such Sharing Party delivers written notice to Jicarilla Solar 2 that such Sharing Party intends to
6
commence utilizing the Shared Facilities (the ???Use Exercise Notice???, which Use Exercise Notice shall set forth the date such use right is to commence (the ???Use Right Date???). As of the Use Right Date, such Party shall (i) have the right to use the Shared Facilities as set forth in Section 3.1, and (ii) become responsible for paying its Pro Rata Share of the Costs in accordance with Section 5.2(i) of this Agreement, to the extent pertaining to the time period after the Use Right Date and for so long as such Party is a Sharing Party hereunder.
3.3 Access Rights Prior To Connection. The Parties acknowledge that the Projects have not been completed as of the Execution Date. Jicarilla Solar 2 hereby grants to each Party for a reasonable period of time prior to the Connection of a Party???s Project, a nonexclusive right to access and use the Shared Facilities to the extent reasonably required to construct and Connect its Project, subject to the following conditions:
(i) At least ninety (90) days prior to Connecting its Project, a Party (each Party in such capacity, a ???Connecting Party???) shall notify Jicarilla Solar 2 in writing of its intent to construct its Project and its need to access and use the Shared Facilities for that purpose (the ???Access Notice???). The Access Notice shall also include a description of the manner in which the Connecting Party intends to construct and Connect its Project to the Shared Facilities, any modifications or upgrades required to be made to the Shared Facilities in order to Connect its Project, and the type and location of the facilities or equipment to be installed. The Connecting Party shall reasonably consider any reasonable request and execute and deliver mutually acceptable documentation with respect to its construction and Connection of its Project as may be reasonably requested by Jicarilla Solar 2, if any, in order to implement the requirements of this Agreement with respect thereto. The Parties agree that any dispute as to whether the Connecting Party has been reasonable in considering suggestions and requests of Jicarilla Solar 2 or whether Jicarilla Solar 2 has been reasonable in its requests to the Connecting Party shall be resolved by the determination of an independent engineer.
(ii) Each Party shall take actions reasonably requested by the other Parties, at no cost to the assisting Party, to effect the Connection of each Project.
(iii) Notwithstanding anything contained herein to the contrary, the Connecting Party shall bear any incremental costs and expenses of modifying and upgrading the Shared Facilities to accommodate the Connection of its Project.
3.4 Essential Nature. Jicarilla Solar 2 hereby acknowledges that the right of each Sharing Party to access and utilize the Shared Facilities is essential to the injection of electric energy from its Operating Project to the transmission system of JANPA and withdrawal of energy by its Operating Project from the JANPA Transmission System.
7
3.5 Vesting. The right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities granted hereunder by Jicarilla Solar 2 shall vest to each Sharing Party as a contracting party hereunder without any transfer of title, leasehold, or other interest or rights in the Shared Facilities, except as otherwise set forth herein.
3.6 Reserved.
3.7 Permitted Capacity Changes. The Parties agree that the Permitted Capacity of any Project will change to reflect any changes in its Project???s nameplate capacity, provided that no Party may increase its Permitted Capacity to a level that would cause the Total Permitted Capacity to exceed 190 MW.
4. RIGHTS AND OBLIGATIONS OF THE PARTIES
4.1 Nature of Services. The Parties acknowledge that the grant of rights under this Agreement by Jicarilla Solar 2 to the Operating Projects is made for the purpose of enabling the energy from their respective Projects to reach the JANPA Transmission System, and for energy from the transmission system of JANPA to reach their respective Projects.
4.2 Obligations of Jicarilla Solar 2. Jicarilla Solar 2 shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner consistent with its obligations under the Jicarilla Solar 2 TCIA, and shall not be required under this Agreement to take any action or refrain from taking any action that would be inconsistent with its obligations under or cause a breach of the Jicarilla Solar 2 TCIA. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, Jicarilla Solar 2 agrees to:
(i) perform its obligations under this Agreement in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations, and Applicable Reliability Standards;
(ii) comply with all provisions of the Jicarilla Solar 2 TCIA (including, without limitation, all insurance requirements, payments due, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof);
(iii) promptly provide to the Sharing Parties any notices it receives under the Jicarilla Solar 2 TCIA from JANPA, PNM or any regulatory authority with jurisdiction over the Shared Facilities that may affect the Sharing Parties or the Shared Facilities including, but not limited to the detail of curtailment order or request in accordance with Section 6.1; and
(iv) perform necessary maintenance on the Shared Facilities and be responsible for operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement, and replacement of the Shared Facilities.
4.3 Obligations of Sharing Parties. Each Sharing Party shall exercise its rights and 8
perform its obligations under this Agreement in a commercially reasonable manner. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, each Sharing Party agrees as follows:
(i) to operate its Operating Project and perform its obligations under this Agreement in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards.
(ii) to use all commercially reasonable efforts to promptly resolve any technical issues arising in connection with its Operating Project that might adversely affect the operation and use of the Shared Facilities;
(iii) to comply with all instructions, as may be communicated to it by Jicarilla Solar 2, in order to ensure compliance with the provisions of the Jicarilla Solar 2 TCIA and this Agreement;
(iv) to provide Jicarilla Solar 2 or a designated representative with all reasonable information reasonably requested by Jicarilla Solar 2 regarding the operation and condition of its Operating Project or expected operation and condition of its Operating Project that is required for Jicarilla Solar 2 to maintain compliance with the terms and conditions of the Jicarilla Solar 2 TCIA;
(v) promptly provide to Jicarilla Solar 2 copies of all notices and instructions received by the Party that affect Jicarilla Solar 2???s performance under the Jicarilla Solar 2???s TCIA;
(vi) if any Sharing Party???s Project is using the Shared Facilities in excess of its Permitted Capacity under this Agreement or in an unpermitted fashion, then such Sharing Party shall immediately upon obtaining knowledge thereof cause such excess or unpermitted usage by its Operating Project to be discontinued, reduced, interrupted, and/or curtailed, as applicable, it being understood and agreed by the Parties that the operation of an Operating Project by Sharing Party at levels that temporarily exceed such Sharing Party???s Permitted Capacity but does not impair the operating levels of the other Operating Projects will not be deemed a breach of this Agreement by such Sharing Party.
4.4 No Joint and Several Liability. The Parties acknowledge that this Agreement does not subject either Party to joint and several liability for any actions taken by the other Party.
4.5 Interference. Subject to the terms of this Agreement, in no event shall any Party be entitled to exercise its rights to access and utilize the Shared Facilities if the exercise of such rights would interfere with or limit the reasonable and necessary access and utilization of the
9
Shared Facilities by any other Party.
4.6 Prior Written Consent. Except as otherwise set forth in this Agreement, without the prior written consent of each other Party, no Party shall take any action that results in (a) the forbearance, foreclosure, termination, or alteration of the respective rights of another Party or (b) increases the obligations or responsibilities of another Party, in each case, with respect to such Party???s access to, utilization of, or reliance upon the Shared Facilities.
4.7 Successor Agreement.
(i) In the event that the Shared Facilities are no longer operated and maintained only by Jicarilla Solar 2 for any reason, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate mutually agreeable terms and execute a mutually agreeable agreement (or amendment to this Agreement) that specifies the division of responsibilities of the entities providing operation and maintenance services associated with the Shared Facilities.
(ii) When an Operating Project no longer requires access to or use of the Shared Facilities, it will cease being an Operating Project and the Person that owns such Operating Project shall cease to be a Sharing Party. The Parties agree to use good faith efforts to amend the Agreement to the extent necessary to reflect this event.
4.8 Change in Law. In the event that a change in the laws or regulations applicable to the Shared Facilities, any of the Operating Projects, or this Agreement requires the amendment, modification, or replacement of this Agreement in order to satisfy any applicable federal, state, tribal or other local regulatory requirements, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms to accomplish such amendment, modification, or replacement.
4.9 Metering Protocol. Each Operating Project will have its own meter located on the ???low side??? of the transformer that is part of the Shared Facilities. A single meter to be located on the ???high side??? of such transformer will aggregate the energy output of all Operating Projects and reflect transformer losses. The Parties agree to enter into a separate metering protocol to address (A) the energy output and usage of the applicable Operating Projects, (B) associated losses, and (C) payments associated with the Operating Projects??? energy output, usage, and losses.
5. ALLOCATION OF COSTS, EXPENSES, AND LOSSES
5.1 [Reserved].
5.2 Allocation of Shared Facilities Costs.
(i) In accordance with Section 4.4(iv), Jicarilla Solar 2 is responsible for the operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, 10
improvement, and replacement of the Shared Facilities; provided, however, that the Parties hereby agree that (a) the costs and expenses of the operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement, and replacement of the Shared Facilities and (b) the costs and expenses of insuring the Shared Facilities, and ((a) and(b) collectively, ???Costs???), and which are not directly caused by an identified Party under this Agreement, shall be shared between and among the Jicarilla 2 and each Sharing Party with an Operating Project on a pro rata basis such that each such Party???s pro rata share is its Permitted Capacity divided by the sum of the Permitted Capacity of all Operating Projects (???Pro Rata Share???). Each Party shall be responsible for all Costs that are directly caused by such Party or its respective Operating Project. Within thirty (30) days of receipt of written notice specifying such Costs from Jicarilla Solar 2 (x) each Party shall pay its Pro Rata Share of Costs, and (y) each Party shall pay the Costs directly attributed to that Party.
(ii) Each Party shall be liable to pay for the station power service of its Project.
5.3 Reimbursement for Net Revenue Losses
(i) A Party (each Party in such capacity, a ???Connected Party???) shall reimburse any other Party (each Party in such capacity, an ???Affected Party???) for all Net Revenue Losses accruing during the period of disconnection, interruption, or curtailment of the Affected Party???s Project arising from any Connection of the Connected Party???s Project due to construction, operation, maintenance activities, use of the Shared Facilities, or entry upon any Shared Facilities (each event, an ???Interruption???), it being hereby agreed that payment of the Net Revenue Losses as defined herein shall be the Affected Party???s sole and exclusive remedy with respect to loss of revenue and other consequential damages due to the period of Interruption. The Parties agree that the actual consequential damages arising due to such period of Interruption would be difficult to compute and that the methodology for determining such damages set forth above is a good faith estimate of the calculations utilized to determine the actual consequential damages that would be suffered.
(ii) ???Net Revenue Losses??? shall include all revenues that an Affected Party would have earned or other costs incurred in connection with lost sales, including: (a) revenues that an Affected Party would have earned for energy, green attributes, capacity, or other products it would have sold under applicable agreements to which it is a party, (b) availability incentive or bonus payments lost, or (c) other penalties, costs, or charges incurred by such Affected Party, as a direct result of any (x) Interruption,
11
or (y) Breach; in each case, such payments made or to be made shall be reduced by any insurance proceeds actually received by such Party in connection with the events described in clauses (x) and (y) of this section.
(iii) In the event that one or more Parties are responsible for an Interruption, Jicarilla Solar 2, acting reasonably, will and on the basis of data collected from ???low side??? meters, will allocate the Net Revenue Losses to any Party that is responsible for the Interruption. If, however, it is not reasonably possible for Jicarilla Solar 2 to accurately allocate such responsibility for an Interruption or a Party reasonably disputes the determination made by Jicarilla Solar 2, such Net Revenue Losses shall be allocated according to the determination of an independent engineering firm selected by Jicarilla Solar 2 and reasonably acceptable to the Parties, whose determination shall be final and binding on the Parties. The fees charged by such independent engineering firm shall be borne by the Sharing Party whose Operating Project was determined to be responsible for the Interruption, and if more than one is determined to be responsible, pro rata by such the relevant Sharing Parties in accordance with their respective Permitted Capacities.
5.4 FERC Annual Charges. Each Sharing Party shall reimburse Jicarilla Solar 2 for its share of the actual amount of FERC annual charges, if any, that are assessed to Jicarilla Solar 2 in connection with the Shared Facilities. A Sharing Party???s share for the purposes of this section will be based on the ratio of the energy output of each Sharing Party???s Operating Project during the FERC billing period to the total energy output of all Operating Projects during the same FERC billing period.
6. CURTAILMENTS
6.1 Curtailments.
(i) An Operating Project shall interrupt or reduce its deliveries of electrical power over the Shared Facilities if requested to do so by Jicarilla Solar 2 in accordance with the following provisions: (a) after reasonable notice to the Operating Project as to the timing and duration of the curtailment, to maintain, repair, replace, remove, investigate, inspect, or test any part of the Shared Facilities in accordance with the terms of this Agreement; or (b) if any Party is ordered to do so by JANPA, PNM or any regulatory authority with jurisdiction over the Shared Facilities.
(ii) In either the case of (a) or (b), Jicarilla Solar 2 shall limit the length of any such curtailment to that time strictly necessary to correct the problem.
(iii) Any curtailment made pursuant to clause (a) above shall be made to the extent commercially reasonable during periods that balance both low or
12
no solar resource and low energy prices so as to minimize potential loss of revenue of the Operating Projects being curtailed.
(iv) Unless directed otherwise by JANPA, PNM or any regulatory authority with jurisdiction over the Shared Facilities, Jicarilla Solar 2 shall allocate curtailment orders issued under clauses (a) and (b) of Section 6.1(i) among each Operating Project in accordance with such Operating Project???s Pro Rata Share; provided, however, that (x) the Permitted Capacity of an Operating Project that has not reached its Commercial Operation Date shall be excluded from such calculation of Pro Rata Share for the purposes of this sentence, and (y) such Operating Project that has not reached its Commercial Operation Date shall be curtailed in its entirety prior to any curtailment of any Operating Projects that have reached their Commercial Operation Date.
7. CERTAIN COVENANTS
7.1 Authority and Operational Abilities. Each Party represents, as of the Effective Date, and covenants for the term of this Agreement, that such Party has the legal authority and operational abilities to fulfill its obligations under this Agreement.
7.2 FERC Approval. No later than thirty (30) days after Jicarilla Solar 2 commences construction on the Jicarilla Solar 2 Project, Jicarilla Solar 2 will file this Agreement with FERC as a rate schedule under FPA ?? 205 (the ???Rate Schedule Filing???) unless Jicarilla Solar 2 is advised by FERC counsel that such filing is not required by applicable law. Each Sharing Party agrees to reasonably cooperate with Jicarilla Solar 2 in connection with the Rate Schedule Filing. Each Party acknowledges that (a) this Agreement will be publicly available through such Rate Schedule Filing; (b) after the Rate Schedule Filing has been made, any subsequent amendments to this Agreement must be filed with and accepted by FERC, and the effectiveness of such amendments will be contingent on such FERC acceptance; and (c) disconnections or terminations contemplated by this Agreement may require prior FERC approval.
7.3 Agreement to Cooperate. Each Party agrees to reasonably cooperate with the other Parties so that, subject to the terms of this Agreement, each Operating Project benefits from the full utilization and enjoyment of the Shared Facilities as is necessary for the efficient operation of each such Operating Project.
8. BREACHES
8.1 Breach by any Party. EXHIBIT A TO SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT
Shared Facilities The ???Shared Facilities??? shall consist of the following: 1. A 345/34.5 kV transformer, 345 kV breaker and 345 kV tie line from such transformer to the Point of Interconnection as defined in each Project???s TCIA or Transmission Service Agreement. The 190 MVA transformer (114700/152900/191000 kVA ) transforms voltage 345-34.5 kV NL- 80kW LL-265kW. The Manufacturer was VIRGINIA - GEORGIA TRANSFORMER and it was designed and fabricated in accordance with all applicable ANSI/IEEE standards.
The SF6 gas 345 kV Breaker is a 362 kV Dead Tank Circuit Breakers according to ANSI/IEEE standards for outdoor installation with mechanical spring operating mechanism to allow for common components between the various voltage levels. The circuit breaker is qualified to M2 class for mechanical endurance in accordance with IEC 62271-100. The circuit breaker is qualified to C2 class for lines and cables in accordance with IEEE/ANSI C37. The circuit breaker guaranteed SF6 loss is <0.5% per year certified by calibrated measurement in GE proprietary gas tightness testing chamber.
The 345kV transmission line shall be 3- phase conductors consisting of double-bundle conductor with two 795kcmil ACSR DRAKE conductors. The conductors are non-specular to minimize light reflection and are arranged in a vertical configuration to avoid the need for mid- span spacers and have stockbridge dampers to mitigate conductor damage from aeolian vibration.
Transmission towers are multi-pole, weathering steel, tangent and dead-end/angle structures with the phase conductors arranged horizontally and two shield conductors located above the phase conductors. H-frame structures for tangent structures and steel, three-pole structures for dead-ends and angles are directly embedded and supported by concrete/rebar pier-type foundations respectively.
Shield wires are one 1/2??? extra high strength steel wire and one 144-count optical ground wire oriented to adequately protect the phase conductors from lightning flashes.
2. Collector Substation: The collector substation contains the 345/34.5 kV main power transformer, HV SF6 circuit breaker, HV disconnect switch, surge arresters, instrument transformers, MV circuit breakers, MV disconnect switches, and auxiliary systems including cable and raceways, grounding, lightning protection, auxiliary power, and lighting.
1
A 15.6??? by 36??? pre-engineered metal control building houses panels/panelboards for each project (Solar 2, Solar 1, and BESS 1) for the DC systems, SCADA/communications/metering systems, protection and control systems. Station service AC distribution system and auxiliary systems (lighting, HVAC, backup power batteries, and security/safety monitoring) control panels are also provided.
3. Security Fencing: The site is enclosed by a 6-foot high permanent chain link fence topped with 1-foot 3-strand barbed wire. Fencing under transmission lines is isolated and grounded according to Utility requirements and NESC standards. It is commercial grade, minimum Schedule 40 pipe with minimum yield strength of 25,000 pounds per square inch and protected with zinc. Array access is provided by a lockable 24-foot double swing gates. Keyed padlocks are provided for each installed gate, and at third party utility line crossings. 4. Switchyard and fencing: A 190??? by 290??? switchyard with crushed aggregate surface contains the equipment and control building as described in 2, Collector Substation. The switchyard is fully grounded with a 30??? grid and 4/0 pigtails.
The substation fencing surrounds the entire yard and is 8-feet high permanent chain link fence topped with 1-foot 3-strand barbed wire in accordance with local Utility requirements and NESC standards. Fencing under transmission lines is isolated and grounded according to Utility requirements and NESC standards, attached to the grounding grid at a minimum of 50??? o.c. Fence is commercial grade, minimum Schedule 40 pipe with minimum yield strength of 25,000 pounds per square inch and protected with zinc. Two keyed padlocked 24-foot double swing gates provides access.

Market-Based Rate Wholesale Power Sale Tariff
1. Availability. Jicarilla Solar 2 LLC ("Seller") makes electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services available under this Tariff to any purchaser for resale. 2. Applicability. This Tariff is applicable to all sales of capacity, energy, or ancillary services by Seller not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule. 3. Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sales shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 5. Ancillary Services. Seller may make available to any purchaser the following ancillary services. a. California: Seller offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation ("CAISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO. b. New York: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc. c. New England: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc. d. PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. e. MISO: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. (???MISO???) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO. f. Southwest Power Pool: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (???SPP???) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP. g. Third Party Provider: Seller offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve-Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider???s OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization. 6. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. Seller has received (i) waiver of the accounting and reporting requirements contained in 18 C.F.R. Parts 41, 101 (with the exception that waiver of the provisions of Part 101 that apply to hydropower licensees is not granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects), and 141, except for Sections 141.14 and 141.15; (ii) waiver of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subparts B and C, except for Sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; and (iii) blanket authorization under 18 C.F.R. Part 34 of all future issuances of securities and assumption of liabilities. See Jicarilla Solar 2 LLC, Docket No. ER22-871-000 (2022). 8. Seller Category. Seller is a Category 1 seller in the Central, Northeast, Northwest, Southeast, Southwest, and Southwest Power Pool regions, as defined by 18 C.F.R. ?? 35.36(a).
